  "doc_id": "51098",
  "text": "We began screening a wide range of ionic liquids to perform the Barbier-type In-mediated allylation. Thus, when allyl bromide and benzaldehyde were mixed with indium powder in [bmim] [BF 4 ] (where bmim = 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium), the corresponding homoallylic alcohol 1 was obtained in good yield and in a shorter time (5 h) than that previously reported [CITATION_1] (entry 1, Table 1 including halides, are required in the crotylation of aldehydes depending on the nature of the ionic liquid employed.",
